&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: The successful applicant will be expected to: (i) assist with teaching, laboratory practicals/demonstration and tutorials in (a) &lt;strong&gt;Theory of Structures&lt;/strong&gt; and (b) &lt;strong&gt;Analysis &amp; Design of Structures&lt;/strong&gt;, (ii) mark students’ scripts and laboratory reports, and (iii) perform any responsibilities as may be assigned by the Head of Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;: (i) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;At least a BEng/BSc with 2.2 or better in Civil Engineering, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;(ii) Prior teaching experience as a teaching/graduate assistant and/or sustained industrial experience in a reputable Civil Engineering consulting firm or research institute, and (iii) registered or eligible for registration with a professional engineering body.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

